#. Tag: title
#: guides.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a &HTML; Slideshow"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Turn an existing presentation into standard &HTML; pages with accompanying "
"navigation aids."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First, either make a new presentation, or open an existing one. Then, click on "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export as HTML...</guimenuitem>"
"</menuchoice>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "You will then get a dialog box asking for a few details:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: guides.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Fill in the details for your &HTML; slideshow</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: guides.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Fill in the details for your &HTML; slideshow</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fill in <guilabel>Title</guilabel> and <guilabel>Author</guilabel> "
"fields. Select the slides which should be exported. If you want to change a "
"name used on the &HTML; page for each slide double click on the name and edit "
"it inline."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guilabel>Output preview</guilabel> area the downsized slides are "
"displayed and you can check the correct slide order and browse the presentation "
"with the <guiicon>&lt;</guiicon> and <guiicon>&gt;</guiicon> buttons."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can select a stylesheet with the configuration of the &HTML; options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To actually produce your &HTML; presentation, press the <guibutton>"
"Export</guibutton> button and select a folder."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What we now have are the newly-produced <filename>html/</filename> "
"and <filename>pics/</filename> folders, created where we earlier set the path:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: guides.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The newly created &HTML; slideshow folders</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: guides.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The newly created &HTML; slideshow folders</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also an <filename>index.html</filename> file to launch your web "
"slideshow."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can see how it works by using your file manager or web browser to open the "
"<filename>index.html</filename> file. Click where prompted, and the first slide "
"of your presentation is displayed. It will now behave as a &stage; slideshow."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each click on the arrow icons take you to the next or previous slide. To get "
"back to the start of the slideshow click on the slide icon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To share your presentation with the world, transfer the newly-produced files to "
"a network-accessible location (&ie; webspace), remembering to keep the folder "
"structure intact."
msgstr ""

